32// Note that 'abcd' are dummy characters in place of control characters.
33static const char ALPHABET[] = "0123456789ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ-. $/+%abcd*";
34
35/**
36* Each character consist of 3 bars and 3 spaces and is 9 modules wide in total.
37* Each bar and space is from 1 to 4 modules wide.
38* These represent the encodings of characters. Each module is asigned 1 bit.
39* The 9 least-significant bits of each int correspond to the 9 modules in a symbol.
40* Note: bit 9 (the first) is always 1, bit 1 (the last) is always 0.
41*/
42static const int CHARACTER_ENCODINGS[] = {
43 0x114, 0x148, 0x144, 0x142, 0x128, 0x124, 0x122, 0x150, 0x112, 0x10A, // 0-9
44 0x1A8, 0x1A4, 0x1A2, 0x194, 0x192, 0x18A, 0x168, 0x164, 0x162, 0x134, // A-J
45 0x11A, 0x158, 0x14C, 0x146, 0x12C, 0x116, 0x1B4, 0x1B2, 0x1AC, 0x1A6, // K-T
46 0x196, 0x19A, 0x16C, 0x166, 0x136, 0x13A, // U-Z
47 0x12E, 0x1D4, 0x1D2, 0x1CA, 0x16E, 0x176, 0x1AE, // - - %
48 0x126, 0x1DA, 0x1D6, 0x132, 0x15E, // Control chars ($)==a, (%)==b, (/)==c, (+)==d, *
49};
50
51static_assert(Size(ALPHABET) - 1 == Size(CHARACTER_ENCODINGS), "table size mismatch");
52
53static const int ASTERISK_ENCODING = 0x15E;
54
55using CounterContainer = std::array<int, 6>;
56
57static int
58ToPattern(const CounterContainer& counters)
59{
60 // each bar/space is 1-4 modules wide, the sum of all is 9 modules wide
61 int sum = Reduce(counters);
62 int pattern = 0;
63 for (int i = 0, count = (int)counters.size(); i < count; ++i) {
64 int scaled = (counters[i] * 9 + (sum/2)) / sum; // non-float version of RoundToNearest(counters[i] * 9.0f / sum);
65 if (scaled < 1 || scaled > 4) {
66 return -1;
67 }
68 pattern <<= scaled;
69 pattern |= ~(0xffffffff << scaled) * (~i & 1);
70 }
71 return pattern;
72}
73
74static BitArray::Range
75FindAsteriskPattern(const BitArray& row)
76{
77 CounterContainer counters;
78
79 return RowReader::FindPattern(
80 row.getNextSet(row.begin()), row.end(), counters,
81 [](BitArray::Iterator, BitArray::Iterator, const CounterContainer& counters) {
82 return ToPattern(counters) == ASTERISK_ENCODING;
83 });
84}
85
86static bool
87CheckOneChecksum(const std::string& result, int checkPosition, int weightMax)
88{
89 int weight = 1;
90 int checkSum = 0;
91 for (int i = checkPosition - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
92 checkSum += weight * IndexOf(ALPHABET, result[i]);
93 if (++weight > weightMax) {
94 weight = 1;
95 }
96 }
97 return result[checkPosition] == ALPHABET[checkSum % 47];
98}
99
100static bool
101CheckChecksums(const std::string& result)
102{
103 int length = Size(result);
104 return CheckOneChecksum(result, length - 2, 20) && CheckOneChecksum(result, length - 1, 15);
105}
106
107// forward declare here. see ODCode39Reader.cpp. Not put in header to not pollute the public facing API
108bool DecodeExtendedCode39AndCode93(std::string& encoded, const char ctrl[4]);
109
110Result
111Code93Reader::decodeRow(int rowNumber, const BitArray& row, std::unique_ptr<DecodingState>&) const
112{
113 auto range = FindAsteriskPattern(row);
114 if (!range)
115 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
116
117 int xStart = static_cast<int>(range.begin - row.begin());
118 CounterContainer theCounters = {};
119 std::string result;
120 result.reserve(20);
121
122 do {
123 // Read off white space
124 range = RecordPattern(row.getNextSet(range.end), row.end(), theCounters);
125 if (!range)
126 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
127
128 int pattern = ToPattern(theCounters);
129 if (pattern < 0)
130 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
131
132 int i = IndexOf(CHARACTER_ENCODINGS, pattern);
133 if (i < 0)
134 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
135
136 result += ALPHABET[i];
137 } while (result.back() != '*');
138
139 result.pop_back(); // remove asterisk
140
141 // Should be at least one more black module
142 if (range.end == row.end() || !*range.end) {
143 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
144 }
145
146 // Need at least 2 checksum + 1 payload characters
147 if (result.length() < 3)
148 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
149
150 if (!CheckChecksums(result))
151 return Result(DecodeStatus::ChecksumError);
152
153 // Remove checksum digits
154 result.resize(result.length() - 2);
155
156 if (!DecodeExtendedCode39AndCode93(result, "abcd"))
157 return Result(DecodeStatus::FormatError);
158
159 int xStop = static_cast<int>(range.end - row.begin() - 1);
160 return Result(result, rowNumber, xStart, xStop, BarcodeFormat::CODE_93);
161}
162
163constexpr int CHAR_LEN = 6;
164constexpr int CHAR_SUM = 9;
165// pattern where '1' means 'narrow' and '0' means wide
166constexpr auto START_PATTERN = FixedPattern<CHAR_LEN, CHAR_SUM>{1, 1, 1, 1, 4, 1};
167// quite zone is half the width of a character symbol
168constexpr float QUITE_ZONE_SCALE = 0.5f;
169
170Result Code93Reader::decodePattern(int rowNumber, const PatternView &row, std::unique_ptr<DecodingState> &) const
171{
172 // minimal number of characters that must be present (including start, stop, checksum and 1 payload characters)
173 int minCharCount = 5;
174 auto isStartOrStopSymbol = [](char c) { return c == '*'; };
175 auto decodePattern = [](const PatternView& view) {
176 return LookupBitPattern(OneToFourBitPattern<CHAR_LEN, CHAR_SUM>(view), CHARACTER_ENCODINGS, ALPHABET);
177 };
178
179 auto next = ZXing::FindPattern(row.subView(0, -minCharCount * CHAR_LEN), START_PATTERN, QUITE_ZONE_SCALE);
180 if (!next.isValid())
181 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
182
183 if (!isStartOrStopSymbol(decodePattern(next))) // read off the start pattern
184 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
185
186 int xStart = next.pixelsInFront();
187
188 std::string txt;
189 txt.reserve(20);
190
191 do {
192 // check remaining input width
193 if (!next.skipSymbol())
194 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
195
196 txt += decodePattern(next);
197 if (txt.back() < 0)
198 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
199 } while (!isStartOrStopSymbol(txt.back()));
200
201 txt.pop_back(); // remove asterisk
202
203 if (Size(txt) < minCharCount - 2)
204 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
205
206 // check termination bar (is present and not wider than about 2 modules) and quite zone
207 next = next.subView(0, CHAR_LEN + 1);
208 if (!next.isValid() || next[CHAR_LEN] > next.sum(CHAR_LEN) / 4 || !next.hasQuiteZoneAfter(QUITE_ZONE_SCALE))
209 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
210
211 if (!CheckChecksums(txt))
212 return Result(DecodeStatus::ChecksumError);
213
214 // Remove checksum digits
215 txt.resize(txt.size() - 2);
216
217 if (!DecodeExtendedCode39AndCode93(txt, "abcd"))
218 return Result(DecodeStatus::FormatError);
219
220 int xStop = next.pixelsInFront() + next.sum() - 1;
221 return Result(txt, rowNumber, xStart, xStop, BarcodeFormat::CODE_93);
222}
